CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper May 20, 1967, pg. 1, reads: "Election Day Scenes... Center Photo shows Independent Democratic Candidate Dozita Frazier, who ran sixth, appears at Madison School polls with his little daughters, Lydia, 7, and Dozita, 4.... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Democratic City Council candidate Dozia Frazier, and his daughters Lydia Frazier and Dozita Frazier holding sign reading "My name is Dozita Frazier, Vote for my Daddy, 35-D City Council," outside polling place at Madison School
